  "description": "Growing protocol for *Basella rubra*, vigorous tropical vine from India's Malabar Coast. Requires warmth (minimum 20°C, optimal 25–35°C) and humidity; unsuitable for temperate field cultivation but thrives in greenhouses, warm regions, and container culture. Produces succulent, heart-shaped leaves and edible red berries. Twines 3–6 meters per season; excellent vertical production system.",
